<h2 class="subtitle">What data do we store about you and why?</h2>

<h3>Biological Gender/Sex</h3>
<p>
  Gender data is used to show the distribution of symptoms between males and females. It is not shown in the statistics and visualizations but could be downloaded as part of the dataset.
</p>

<h3>Age group</h3>
<p>
  Age data are collected to show the distribution of symptoms among age groups. It is not shown in the statistics and visualizations but could be downloaded as part of the dataset.
</p>

<h3>Location Information â€” City/Municipality</h3>
<p>
  Location information is collected to visualize the distribution of symptoms on the map page. You have to personally submit this information and we do not automatically retrieve your data.
</p>

<h3>Test Status</h3>
<p>
  Test Status and results are collected so that we can calculate the percentage of the participants who show symptoms. We display this on a map.
</p>

<h3>Symptoms</h3>
<p>
  The symptoms you submit indicate whether you may be infected with the COVID-19
  virus. The timing of the onset of symptoms also gives an indication of how
  long you've be infected, and might have been contagious. We collect this data and visualize it
  anonymously. This way, the public can gain insight and visualize how big the figures
  can be.
</p>
<div class="border-b border-cvs-red mt-4" style="margin: 2em 0;"></div>
